thread.title_full: Patrick Dempsey is riding in Dempsey Challenge fundraiser

author: Associated Press
title: Patrick Dempsey is riding in Dempsey Challenge fundraiser
text:
LEWISTON, Maine -- Actor Patrick Dempsey saddled up for a 50-miler as the Dempsey Challenge wraps up.
Dempsey is best known as a doctor nicknamed McDreamy on TV's "Grey's Anatomy." He rode Sunday on the final day of the two-day bike-and-run fundraiser in Lewiston, Maine.
The event is a fundraiser for The Patrick Dempsey Center for Cancer Hope & Healing at the Central Maine Medical Center. He and his sisters were inspired to help create the center in 2008 by their mother, who died from cancer last year.
Last year, 3,871 participants in the Dempsey Challenge raised $1.14 million.
Dempsey left "Grey's Anatomy" earlier this year. In addition to racing, he's filming the movie "Bridget Jones's Baby" in London.
